loads\/2015\/06\/CfP_CODL_volume_members.pdf\">Call for Papers (link)<\/a><\/h5>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>We look back with great pleasure to the conference of the project <i>An International Network\u00a0<\/i><i>Studying the Circulation of Dutch Literature <\/i>(CODL) in The Hague, and wish to thank you once again for the part you played in making it a successful and inspirational event. More than a hundred people from fifteen countries attended the conference.<\/p>\n<p>Many thanks to those, who have sent us photos of the conference. We have collected these in a\u00a0digital photo album. You will soon receive an electronic invitation to join this album. If you wish\u00a0to add photos you can upload these directly or send them to our conference address, so we can\u00a0assist you with the uploading. (circulationofdutchliterature@gmail.com)<\/p>\n<p>Jack Mc Martin has written a detailed report on the conference, which you can find on the\u00a0CODL site http:\/\/www.codl.nl\/codl-conference-the-hague-28-30-may-2015 . We would be\u00a0happy to hear about any other reactions. Sergei Tcherkasski has asked us to share these two links\u00a0of the <i>Op Hoop van Zegen <\/i>production by his students at the St. Petersburg Theatre Arts Academy:\u00a0https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=XzKXQwDSBKc\u00a022 min (Act 4 of the play) &#8211; http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=0na8eT30540<\/p>\n<p>We are pleased to announce that an English volume of selected articles from the CODL-project\u00a0will be published, edited by the project coordinators.<\/p>\n<h5>Please find here\u00a0the link to the Call for Papers in Dutch:\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.codl.nl\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/06\/CfP_CODL_volume_members.pdf\">Call for Papers (link)<\/a><\/h5>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We kijken met veel plezier terug op uw deelname aan het congres An International Network Studying the Circulation of Dutch Literature (CODL). In totaal waren er ongeveer honderd deelnemers uit vijf